alert.note: Alert for Le Sueur; Scott; Sibley (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued May 22 at 11:27AM CDT until May 23 at 8:30AM CDT by NWS Minneapolis
info.description: ...The Flood Warning is extended for the following rivers in Minnesota... Minnesota River at Savage affecting Scott, Carver, Hennepin and Dakota Counties. Minnesota River near Jordan affecting Scott, Carver and Sibley Counties. Minnesota River at Henderson MN19 affecting Scott, Sibley and Le Sueur Counties. ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Minnesota and Wisconsin... Mississippi River near Hastings L/D 2 (COE) affecting Washington, Pierce, Dakota and Goodhue Counties. Mississippi River at St. Paul affecting Washington, Ramsey and Dakota Counties. .Rivers have crested and will continue to fall this week. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL TOMORROW MORNING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Minnesota River at Henderson MN19. * WHEN...Until tomorrow morning. * IMPACTS...At 732.0 feet, Water begins impacting residences and agricultural buildings north and south of Henderson. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1030 AM CDT Monday, the stage was 732.2 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 1030 AM CDT Monday was 732.5 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage this afternoon and continue falling to 726.2 feet Monday morning. - Flood stage is 732.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 732.1 feet on 04/04/1998. &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas.
